[1] Brazil - Sao Paulo (coast)
Date: 22 Mar 2007
From: LISAS
Source: O Estado de Sao Paulo [trans. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.estadao.com.br/ultimas/index.htm?NotCodigo=42&NotData=2007-03-22>

The 1st fatal dengue case in the state in 2007 was confirmed this
week [week of 18 Mar 2007] in a tourist who contracted the disease in
Itanhaem (south coast) and died on 1 Mar 2007.
On Monday (19 Mar 2007), the Ubatuba Prefecture (north coast)
declared an epidemic situation. Since January (2007), 1800 people
have presented symptoms of this illness, and 286 have had the disease
[dengue] confirmed. The number of [dengue] cases in the municipality
are triple those registered last year (2006). There are 2 suspected
cases of DHF.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
