[2] Brazil - Sao Paulo
Date: 20 Mar 2007
From: Marcia Carlos <marcancarlos@yahoo.com.br>
Source: Folha Online [edited]
<http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/folha/cotidiano/ult95u133158.shtml>

The number of dengue cases in Sao Paulo State have increased 46
percent in less than a week, according to the State Secretary of
Health. On Wednesday [14 Mar 2007], there were 5326 cases, and the
number of cases reached 7808 on Monday [18 Mar 2007]. In the previous
week [week of 11 Mar 2007], there were about 2000 cases.
The cities with the most cases this year [2007] are Sao Birigui (804
[cases]), Aracatuba (724), and Ilha Solteira (485), all in the
northeastern part of the state.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[ProMED-Port cited CruzeiroNet of 17 Mar 2007
<http://www.cruzeironet.com.br/run/5/253587.shl>,
which indicated that the number of dengue cases in Sao Paulo [state]
increased 167 per cent between 2 and 16 Mar [2007]. During this
period, 4887 people have contracted the disease in 160 Sao Paulo
[state] cities. In just the last week (9-16 Mar 2007), 2482 people
were ill, increasing the number of positive [dengue] cases to 7808
throughout the state since 1 Jan 2007. - Mod.TY]
