[4] Chile - Easter Island
Date: 19 Mar 2007
From: ProMED <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Chile.com [trans. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.chile.com/tpl/articulo/detalle/ver.tpl?cod_articulo=87084>

Dr. Cecilia Perret, Faculty of Medicine of the Catholic University,
assured everyone that the 2nd outbreak of dengue detected on Easter
Island [Isla de Pascua] from 2000 until the present does not imply
any danger [from the disease] for the inhabitants of mainland Chile.
"There is a 2nd dengue outbreak, but it is [caused by] the same
[dengue virus] type that appeared in 2000, which explains why there
are so few cases, since the majority of the population is immune, so
mainland Chile does not run any risk [of dengue]."
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
