[5] Nicaragua
Date: 21 Mar 2007
From: A-Lan Banks <A-Lan.Banks@thomson.com>
Source: Prensa Latina - Havana, Cuba [edited]
<http://www.plenglish.com/article.asp?ID=
percent7B3F96F866-7031-44B8-961D-04841A6C77FF percent7D&language=EN>

The Nicaraguan capital Managua and several municipalities of the
western country are on an epidemiologic alert after the deaths of 2
children with hemorrhagic dengue and the detection of another 20
cases of the classical variant of the illness.
The deceased were a 6-year-old girl and a boy of 4 in Managua in
recent days, according to the Public health Minister (MINSA).
About 20 people with dengue are in the capital and the San Rafael del
Sur, Masachapa and Tipitapa areas. A red alert was declared for the
affected municipalities, according to MINSA authorities.
Local authorities exhorted the population to support the
institution's efforts to eradicate the mosquito _Aedes aegypti_, the
main transmitter of the illness.
Cleaning and fumigation campaigns are announced in the whole city for
the next weeks as part of those actions.
--
